These are some of the typical
Gadget ad features,

00:22:17.167 --> 00:22:20.334
that they're contextual...

00:22:22.601 --> 00:22:25.501
And I'm sure everybody here
understands that concept.

00:22:25.501 --> 00:22:27.267
Geo-awareness

00:22:27.267 --> 00:22:30.400
is becoming more and more
important with ads.

00:22:30.400 --> 00:22:33.234
I'm not supposed to mention
certain client names,

00:22:33.234 --> 00:22:34.567
but, for example,

00:22:34.567 --> 00:22:38.267
there's one very large
online auction company

00:22:38.267 --> 00:22:42.801
that sells cars online,

00:22:42.801 --> 00:22:45.400
and they, of course,

00:22:45.400 --> 00:22:47.167
you know,
when somebody buys a car,

00:22:47.167 --> 00:22:49.801
they don't want to drive
six hours to pick it up.

00:22:49.801 --> 00:22:52.234
They want something
in their location.

00:22:52.234 --> 00:22:55.501
So, uh...

00:22:55.501 --> 00:22:59.133
the ads
from the AdWords network

00:22:59.133 --> 00:23:01.467
are given these parameters--

00:23:01.467 --> 00:23:04.267
city, region,
or latitude and longitude.

00:23:04.267 --> 00:23:07.834
It's getting easier and easier
to find out where the user is.

00:23:07.834 --> 00:23:10.767
Gadget ads typically

00:23:10.767 --> 00:23:14.334
have to query a custom API
or Google Base

00:23:14.334 --> 00:23:16.200
with--you know,
probably with a keyword,

00:23:16.200 --> 00:23:18.300
and then obviously
it has to display something,

00:23:18.300 --> 00:23:22.701
you know, the items, the image,
or where it's located.

