If we show you information

00:24:58.501 --> 00:25:00.501
that you can get a ticket
for this price,

00:25:00.501 --> 00:25:02.868
it's probably
some valuable data for you.

00:25:02.868 --> 00:25:06.334
And, of course,
for the customer, for Kayak,

00:25:06.334 --> 00:25:07.767
it's also very valuable,

00:25:07.767 --> 00:25:10.868
because you're more likely
to interact with this type of ad

00:25:10.868 --> 00:25:14.567
than with just some text
that is not really contextual.

00:25:14.567 --> 00:25:16.334
So it's just an example.

00:25:16.334 --> 00:25:18.834
We've been doing a couple
of design of those.

00:25:18.834 --> 00:25:21.634
Again, if we were to tell you
about some of those,

00:25:21.634 --> 00:25:22.901
we'd have to kill you,

00:25:22.901 --> 00:25:26.567
so it would not be very pleasant
for this demonstration.

00:25:26.567 --> 00:25:28.968
So Michael
discussed extensively

00:25:28.968 --> 00:25:31.801
about what we've done
for concerting, contracting.

00:25:31.801 --> 00:25:35.234
We've been also doing
different type of work

00:25:35.234 --> 00:25:37.434
in the past few years,

00:25:37.434 --> 00:25:40.501
and especially creating
our own products.

00:25:40.501 --> 00:25:41.968
In fact,
that's how we started.

00:25:41.968 --> 00:25:44.567
We've been very active
in the iGoogle scene,

00:25:44.567 --> 00:25:47.367
creating gadgets for
your personalized home pages.

00:25:47.367 --> 00:25:48.834
And when you do that,

00:25:48.834 --> 00:25:50.901
what is pretty cool
is you don't have

00:25:50.901 --> 00:25:53.200
a customer
telling you what to do.

00:25:53.200 --> 00:25:55.734
It's, you know, your own idea
that you can implement.

00:25:55.734 --> 00:25:57.133
You can be creative.

00:25:57.133 --> 00:26:01.767
The issue, then, we want
to monetize on these ideas.

00:26:05.300 --> 00:26:07.400
So the concept
is very different, right?

00:26:07.400 --> 00:26:10.067
Nobody will be paying the bill
for you to develop the product,

00:26:10.067 --> 00:26:11.534
so you have
to invest some time.

00:26:11.534 --> 00:26:12.801
But it plays very well

00:26:12.801 --> 00:26:14.634
when you're doing
concerting or contracting,

00:26:14.634 --> 00:26:16.067
because you'll have
some downtime.

00:26:16.067 --> 00:26:19.400
For some weeks, you won't have
any concerting to do.

00:26:19.400 --> 00:26:22.300
That's a very good time
to reapply techniques

00:26:22.300 --> 00:26:24.000
you learned
on customer projects,

00:26:24.000 --> 00:26:27.634
or to learn
on new technologies

00:26:27.634 --> 00:26:30.701
you can try
to do your own products.

00:26:30.701 --> 00:26:33.501
So we discussed two main ways
of monetizing

00:26:33.501 --> 00:26:36.100
using your ad networks
like AdSense,

00:26:36.100 --> 00:26:37.601
which is pay-per-click,

00:26:37.601 --> 00:26:40.467
PPC, and the other one
we look at as well

00:26:40.467 --> 00:26:43.067
is using affiliate marketing
where you create some links

00:26:43.067 --> 00:26:45.467
to some products
on some retail Website,

00:26:45.467 --> 00:26:48.133
and you get paid
for customer action

00:26:48.133 --> 00:26:50.167
if they buy something

00:26:50.167 --> 00:26:54.100
or if they sign up
or something like that.

00:26:54.100 --> 00:26:57.067
Okay, so let's focus first
on iGoogle

00:26:57.067 --> 00:26:59.467
and what we've been
learning and doing

00:26:59.467 --> 00:27:01.133
for these past few years.

00:27:01.133 --> 00:27:03.267
The main issue
you have on iGoogle,

00:27:03.267 --> 00:27:05.968
you don't have a full Web page
to play with.

00:27:05.968 --> 00:27:08.834
You have a very small,
concentrated space,

00:27:08.834 --> 00:27:11.267
and you are competing with
millions of gadgets all around,

00:27:11.267 --> 00:27:14.801
so the best way to monetize
on the iGoogle Gadget

00:27:14.801 --> 00:27:17.067
is to do that elsewhere.

00:27:17.067 --> 00:27:19.701
In many situation,
you'll be doing a gadget

00:27:19.701 --> 00:27:23.234
because you have a blog
or some content on a Website,

00:27:23.234 --> 00:27:25.601
and you just want
to allow your users

00:27:25.601 --> 00:27:27.434
to syndicate your content

00:27:27.434 --> 00:27:30.601
and to see what you have new
when they visit iGoogle.

00:27:30.601 --> 00:27:34.701
When you do that, you know,
the user will be, you know,

00:27:34.701 --> 00:27:36.734
more reminded
about your content

00:27:36.734 --> 00:27:38.334
through the day
when they visit iGoogle,

00:27:38.334 --> 00:27:40.100
and you will get
some crazy traffic

00:27:40.100 --> 00:27:41.934
from iGoogle to your site.

00:27:41.934 --> 00:27:44.634
Something else
that is pretty cool with that

00:27:44.634 --> 00:27:47.567
is once you have enough users
using your gadget,

00:27:47.567 --> 00:27:50.601
and they are leaving good
comments about your gadget,

00:27:50.601 --> 00:27:54.234
you will be ranked pretty good
in the directory,

00:27:54.234 --> 00:27:56.734
meaning new users
will find your, you know,

00:27:56.734 --> 00:27:58.467
your tool, your content,

00:27:58.467 --> 00:28:00.868
and you're pretty likely
to get more users.

00:28:00.868 --> 00:28:03.334
More users,
more traffic, more money.

00:28:03.334 --> 00:28:06.067
So, yeah, again,
if you have a Website

00:28:06.067 --> 00:28:08.767
where you can monetize,
let's take this approach.

00:28:08.767 --> 00:28:11.634
Monetize on the full page
of your content of your blog,

00:28:11.634 --> 00:28:15.601
and just do the gadget
to get some traffic.

00:28:15.601 --> 00:28:16.801
We'll talk in a few seconds

00:28:16.801 --> 00:28:18.534
about how to monetize
in a gadget,

00:28:18.534 --> 00:28:20.901
which is more tricky.

00:28:20.901 --> 00:28:22.901
But quick tips for iGoogle.

00:28:22.901 --> 00:28:24.501
You know,
what we found works well

00:28:24.501 --> 00:28:26.701
is don't try to do something
too big at first.

00:28:26.701 --> 00:28:27.968
Try to find a niche,

00:28:27.968 --> 00:28:32.601
and be good at doing
these little, small specialties.

00:28:32.601 --> 00:28:34.200
And then
you can always expand.

00:28:34.200 --> 00:28:35.701
That's always easy to do.

00:28:35.701 --> 00:28:37.968
Something else
also to consider,

00:28:37.968 --> 00:28:40.267
when you are just
starting development,

00:28:40.267 --> 00:28:41.934
playing with these type
of technologies,

00:28:41.934 --> 00:28:44.234
you know,
you're playing, right?

00:28:44.234 --> 00:28:45.767
But once you start monetizing,

00:28:45.767 --> 00:28:48.801
the users you will get
become your customers,

00:28:48.801 --> 00:28:50.901
that thanks to these people,
you will be making some money,

00:28:50.901 --> 00:28:52.834
so treat them as such,
you know?

00:28:52.834 --> 00:28:54.601
Listen to what
they have to say.

00:28:54.601 --> 00:28:57.300
Make sure that they have
a way to email you,

00:28:57.300 --> 00:29:00.200
to contact you with
some feedback, some questions.

00:29:00.200 --> 00:29:02.267
Also, you know,
you have to monitor

00:29:02.267 --> 00:29:04.100
the Web pages and the directory

00:29:04.100 --> 00:29:06.067
where they can
post comment and rating,

00:29:06.067 --> 00:29:08.234
and try to, you know,
on a regular basis,

00:29:08.234 --> 00:29:09.234
reply to that, you know.

00:29:09.234 --> 00:29:10.734
If they have questions,
answer them.

00:29:10.734 --> 00:29:13.701
If you have concerns or so,
address that.

00:29:13.701 --> 00:29:16.200
I think it's very important
to be successful.

00:29:16.200 --> 00:29:18.033
These users
are your customers,

00:29:18.033 --> 00:29:19.934
so take good care of them.

00:29:19.934 --> 00:29:21.567
So let's now discuss

00:29:21.567 --> 00:29:24.033
about how to monetize
inside the gadget.

00:29:24.033 --> 00:29:26.167
So we'll go through
a few examples.

00:29:26.167 --> 00:29:28.501
This first one is one
of the first I developed.

00:29:28.501 --> 00:29:29.501
It's a wall clock.

00:29:29.501 --> 00:29:31.534
You know,
it became very popular.

00:29:31.534 --> 00:29:33.968
On this one,

00:29:33.968 --> 00:29:37.234
I've been using AdSense
as a way to monetize.

00:29:37.234 --> 00:29:39.734
So, you know, AdSense,
the way it works,

00:29:39.734 --> 00:29:40.934
it looks at the context,

00:29:40.934 --> 00:29:43.167
the keywords around,
you know, the content,

00:29:43.167 --> 00:29:44.400
and find something relevant.

00:29:44.400 --> 00:29:48.100
If you've been using AdSense
on Websites

00:29:48.100 --> 00:29:50.767
and you stop using AdSense
on a gadget,

00:29:50.767 --> 00:29:53.033
you'll be probably
very shocked at first

00:29:53.033 --> 00:29:55.200
to see the CTR,
the click through rate,

00:29:55.200 --> 00:29:56.934
it's extremely low.

00:29:56.934 --> 00:29:59.334
On the Website,
usually you see a few percent

00:29:59.334 --> 00:30:01.968
of the impression
convert to a click.

00:30:01.968 --> 00:30:03.601
On AdSense at first,

00:30:03.601 --> 00:30:05.667
you know,
I was very surprised to see

00:30:05.667 --> 00:30:08.934
that we have a number
of about 0.05%.

00:30:08.934 --> 00:30:11.100
So, yeah,
it's very, very low.

00:30:11.100 --> 00:30:13.567
But when you think about it,
it makes sense.

00:30:13.567 --> 00:30:17.067
On iGoogle, you have
so much content on the page,

00:30:17.067 --> 00:30:18.567
you don't have the user focused

00:30:18.567 --> 00:30:20.901
on your specific gadget
all the time.

00:30:20.901 --> 00:30:22.601
Even worse than that,
you know,

00:30:22.601 --> 00:30:25.067
you can have
your gadget positioned

00:30:25.067 --> 00:30:26.767
below, you know, the page.

00:30:26.767 --> 00:30:28.667
You have to scroll down
to see it,

00:30:28.667 --> 00:30:29.968
meaning most of the time,

00:30:29.968 --> 00:30:32.567
the user won't see
your gadget or your ad.

00:30:32.567 --> 00:30:35.033
Something else
to keep in mind as well,

00:30:35.033 --> 00:30:38.067
most users,
they keep the iGoogle page

00:30:38.067 --> 00:30:40.534
up all day long,

00:30:40.534 --> 00:30:43.968
and you probably notice
that every seven or ten minutes,

00:30:43.968 --> 00:30:46.601
the page refreshes by itself,

00:30:46.601 --> 00:30:49.067
meaning you will generate
many, many impression

00:30:49.067 --> 00:30:50.968
when nobody's
looking at the page.

00:30:50.968 --> 00:30:52.767
So that's what explains
this low CTR.

00:30:52.767 --> 00:30:54.601
So nothing
to be concerned about.

00:30:54.601 --> 00:30:56.667
That's the way it is.

00:30:59.400 --> 00:31:00.767
Okay.

00:31:00.767 --> 00:31:02.267
Just to give you
some guidelines...

00:31:02.267 --> 00:31:04.000
I don't know
if it's that useful,

00:31:04.000 --> 00:31:06.334
but what we've been saying
for monetization,

00:31:06.334 --> 00:31:10.634
you can expect to get
about 15 bucks per month

00:31:10.634 --> 00:31:12.267
per thousand users.

00:31:12.267 --> 00:31:14.968
When we talk
a thousand users,

00:31:14.968 --> 00:31:17.100
you know,
it will be active users.

00:31:17.100 --> 00:31:19.234
If you look
in your analytics account,

00:31:19.234 --> 00:31:21.934
you know, they show you
the evolution per day.

00:31:21.934 --> 00:31:23.300
Kind of takes the peak,

00:31:23.300 --> 00:31:28.400
and you can assume that the peak
is your active user base.

00:31:28.400 --> 00:31:29.701
Okay?

00:31:29.701 --> 00:31:32.467
This number is, of course,
it's a ballpark figure.

00:31:32.467 --> 00:31:34.701
If you have a gadget
with some content

00:31:34.701 --> 00:31:37.234
that match very
high-paying keywords,

00:31:37.234 --> 00:31:38.834
you may see something
better than we do.

00:31:38.834 --> 00:31:40.801
Good for you.

00:31:40.801 --> 00:31:42.534
But some--
I think some people,

00:31:42.534 --> 00:31:44.133
as you can see,
something less than that.

00:31:44.133 --> 00:31:47.300
It's just probably an average.

00:31:47.300 --> 00:31:49.000
All right.

00:31:49.000 --> 00:31:50.968
Google released
not that long ago

00:31:50.968 --> 00:31:53.501
the canvas view for iGoogle.

00:31:53.501 --> 00:31:57.000
So that's a pretty
powerful feature.

00:31:57.000 --> 00:31:59.100
If you have a gadget
and need more space,

00:31:59.100 --> 00:32:02.033
you can define
an alternate view,

00:32:02.033 --> 00:32:04.067
which will be using
kind of a full page.

00:32:04.067 --> 00:32:06.000
You still have
the Google logo on top

00:32:06.000 --> 00:32:08.467
and a sidebar
on the left-hand side,

00:32:08.467 --> 00:32:11.200
but you have much more
real estate to play with.

00:32:11.200 --> 00:32:13.400
That's an example
from LabPixies.

00:32:13.400 --> 00:32:15.300
It's one of the top
developers for iGoogle,

00:32:15.300 --> 00:32:17.434
and they've made
very good use of that.

00:32:17.434 --> 00:32:19.033
They have a little game

00:32:19.033 --> 00:32:21.901
that on the iGoogle page
is just a small image.

00:32:21.901 --> 00:32:23.601
You cannot
do anything with it.

00:32:23.601 --> 00:32:24.934
But when you click on it,

00:32:24.934 --> 00:32:27.400
it opens a full-time view--
full-screen view,

00:32:27.400 --> 00:32:28.767
and they show you the game

00:32:28.767 --> 00:32:31.968
plus some big-size ad
on the side.

00:32:31.968 --> 00:32:36.200
We can implement that,
continue with that user.

00:32:36.200 --> 00:32:39.567
You know,
but I'm pretty sure

00:32:39.567 --> 00:32:41.667
it's working
pretty well for them.

00:32:41.667 --> 00:32:44.400
It's probably about, you know,
the same as a Web page.

00:32:44.400 --> 00:32:46.767
On the other hand,
the user will see the ad

00:32:46.767 --> 00:32:48.367
only when they interact
with the gadget.

00:32:48.367 --> 00:32:52.501
So we're pretty much back
to when you have a gadget

00:32:52.501 --> 00:32:54.300
driving traffic
to your Website.

00:32:54.300 --> 00:32:56.701
Another example
I wanted to show you

00:32:56.701 --> 00:32:58.501
is using affiliate links.

00:32:58.501 --> 00:33:00.167
So it's a small gadget

00:33:00.167 --> 00:33:02.334
that's designed
just for fun at first.

00:33:02.334 --> 00:33:03.934
I'm a big fan of woot.com.

00:33:03.934 --> 00:33:07.100
I like to see every day,
every morning,

00:33:07.100 --> 00:33:10.167
what they are selling,
so I designed this small gadget,

00:33:10.167 --> 00:33:11.601
and it started working
pretty well,

00:33:11.601 --> 00:33:13.968
so I was thinking,
"How can I monetize?"

00:33:13.968 --> 00:33:15.200
And at the time,

00:33:15.200 --> 00:33:17.634
I already had the wall clocks
with AdSense.

00:33:17.634 --> 00:33:19.701
And even though
it was working well,

00:33:19.701 --> 00:33:21.267
I was still getting,
you know,

00:33:21.267 --> 00:33:24.334
weekly hate emails from users,
saying, you know,

00:33:24.334 --> 00:33:26.934
"It's dirty. Don't put AdSense
on iGoogle," you know.

00:33:26.934 --> 00:33:28.167
People don't like it
that much.

00:33:28.167 --> 00:33:29.801
Of course,
it takes up real estate.

00:33:29.801 --> 00:33:34.567
So I wanted to experiment
with something different.

00:33:34.567 --> 00:33:37.567
You know, I thought
because woot.com customer,

00:33:37.567 --> 00:33:38.934
I know them pretty well.

00:33:38.934 --> 00:33:39.968
They are in the U.S.

00:33:39.968 --> 00:33:42.067
They are people
who like technologies.

00:33:42.067 --> 00:33:44.734
If I can show you
some product

00:33:44.734 --> 00:33:47.667
on Amazon, buy.com,
or you name it,

00:33:47.667 --> 00:33:49.234
they'll probably be interested.

00:33:49.234 --> 00:33:51.467
You know, if I find
the good deals of the moment,

00:33:51.467 --> 00:33:53.601
that will be
good value for them.

00:33:53.601 --> 00:33:56.000
So I started building that
manually every day,

00:33:56.000 --> 00:33:58.501
finding products
and putting links up there.

00:33:58.501 --> 00:34:02.000
And these links are created
through their affiliate Website

00:34:02.000 --> 00:34:05.067
of, you know, as I mentioned,
Amazon or others.

00:34:05.067 --> 00:34:07.234
So when someone
click on the link,

00:34:07.234 --> 00:34:09.334
and if the customer later on

00:34:09.334 --> 00:34:12.033
buy a product on the site
I'm sending them to,

00:34:12.033 --> 00:34:13.067
we get a commission

00:34:13.067 --> 00:34:16.167
ranging from 1% to 8%,
roughly.

00:34:16.167 --> 00:34:18.567
What is, you know,

00:34:18.567 --> 00:34:20.100
I think
is a good takeaway from that

00:34:20.100 --> 00:34:22.334
is I never had anybody

00:34:22.334 --> 00:34:25.501
complain about this type
of advertising in a gadget.

00:34:25.501 --> 00:34:27.033
It's small.
It's looking pretty nice.

00:34:27.033 --> 00:34:30.033
So--But two years
I've been doing that,

00:34:30.033 --> 00:34:32.567
and never receive
a single email from anybody.

00:34:32.567 --> 00:34:34.100
On the other hand,

00:34:34.100 --> 00:34:36.300
the revenue
is not as good either.

00:34:36.300 --> 00:34:39.400
You know,
doing this type of work,

00:34:39.400 --> 00:34:44.400
I'm getting about $2 to $3
per month per thousand users.

00:34:44.400 --> 00:34:45.901
But I think, you know,

00:34:45.901 --> 00:34:49.234
at least the look and feel
is good, and the user are happy,

00:34:49.234 --> 00:34:51.267
so I think
it's a good drawback.

00:34:51.267 --> 00:34:54.367
If you want to try to play
with this type of stuff,

00:34:54.367 --> 00:34:56.534
what I've seen amazon.com,

00:34:56.534 --> 00:34:59.100
by far,
is what is paying the best

00:34:59.100 --> 00:35:00.701
for affiliate marketing,

00:35:00.701 --> 00:35:03.367
just because, you know,
most people will buy something

00:35:03.367 --> 00:35:05.200
from Amazon, so...

00:35:05.200 --> 00:35:08.267
If you send them
to other smaller Website

00:35:08.267 --> 00:35:12.067
like buy.com, newegg.com,
TigerDirect,

00:35:12.067 --> 00:35:15.067
and a few of the bunch,
the conversions aren't as good.

00:35:15.067 --> 00:35:17.033
And so by the way,

00:35:17.033 --> 00:35:19.100
Amazon, they have
their own affiliate program.

00:35:19.100 --> 00:35:22.868
If you want to go
and affiliate with the others,

00:35:22.868 --> 00:35:25.734
you have to use brokers
like Commission Junction,

00:35:25.734 --> 00:35:27.234
CJ,

00:35:27.234 --> 00:35:29.801
linkshare.com as well
is on the brokers.

00:35:29.801 --> 00:35:33.534
And I'm talking here
about technology products.

00:35:33.534 --> 00:35:35.501
But if your site
is about babies

00:35:35.501 --> 00:35:36.734
or about, you know, fashion,

00:35:36.734 --> 00:35:39.434
you know,
they have affiliate programs

00:35:39.434 --> 00:35:41.734
with almost any type
of retailers.

00:35:41.734 --> 00:35:44.133
I was planning to have time
to experiment

